<paragraph blockId="0.[835,1474,1801,2113]" lastBlockId="1.[113,752,554,643]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="80" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,952,1801,1825]" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1938" box="[1103,1266,1801,1825]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Engraulidae" genus="Encrasicholina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clupeiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1103,1266,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Encrasicholina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the following combination of characters: dorsal and anal fins with two unbranched rays; pseudobranchial filaments 21–26 (modally 24); gill rakers 20–23 (20) in upper series on 1st gill arch, 26–28 (26) in lower series, 46–50 (46) in total; gill rakers 13–14 (13) in upper series on 2nd gill arch, 23–25 (23) in lower series, 36–38 (36) in total; gill rakers 10–12 (11) in upper series on 3rd gill arch, 12–13 (13) in lower series, 23–25 (24) in total; gill rakers 9–10 (10) in upper series on 4th gill arch, 9–11 (10) in lower, 19–21 (20) in total; prepelvic scutes 3–6 (5); posterior tip of upper jaw not reaching to anterior margin of preopercle; length of first unbranched dorsal-fin ray 4.7–5.8% of SL.
</paragraph>
